/**
 * Shared translation system for the static UI chrome (nav, headers, section
 * titles, table headers, form labels, buttons, status badges) across all
 * dashboard pages. Auto-generated analytics narrative text (executive
 * summaries, insights, recommendations in course_report.js/program_report.js)
 * is intentionally out of scope here — it's full generated sentences, not
 * fixed labels, and needs its own dual-language generation logic.
 *
 * Usage:
 *   - Static HTML: add data-i18n="key" (textContent) or
 *     data-i18n-placeholder="key" (input placeholder) to an element.
 *   - Dynamic JS-rendered strings: call t('key') instead of hardcoding text.
 *   - Any page with a `.lang-toggle-btn` button gets click-to-toggle wired
 *     up automatically; the language choice persists via localStorage.
 */
